{"questionId":"12144","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><em>In this question you will explore possible models for the spread of an infectious disease</em></p>\n<p>An infectious disease has begun spreading in a country. The National Disease Control Centre (NDCC) has compiled the following data after receiving alerts from hospitals.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0025233698dc6131cb33588b8d65d6d04ae8a12a.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span> against <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"d\">\n  <mi>d</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is shown below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c13964a53d69efdc0f59cf0e2cd757e469be254d.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The NDCC want to find a model to predict the total number of people infected, so they can plan for medicine and hospital facilities. After looking at the data, they think an exponential function in the form <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n = a{b^d}\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> could be used as a model.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The NDCC want to verify the accuracy of these predictions. They decide to perform a <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\chi ^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>χ</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> goodness of fit test.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The predictions given by the model for the first five days are shown in the table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/68e1d8842e90f7d78f4e51f28ecf5aacfcb22403.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Perform a <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\chi ^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>χ</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> goodness of fit test at the 5% significance level. You should clearly state your hypotheses, the p-value, and your conclusion.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{H_0}\\,{\\text{:}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>H</mi>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>:</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;data is modeled by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\\left( d \\right) = 9.7782{\\left( {1.7125} \\right)^d}\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>d</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>9.7782</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1.7125</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{H_1}\\,{\\text{:}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>H</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>:</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;data is not modeled by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\\left( d \\right) = 9.7782{\\left( {1.7125} \\right)^d}\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>d</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>9.7782</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1.7125</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>p-value = 0.893&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p>Since 0.893 &gt; 0.05&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>Insufficient evidence to reject <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{H_0}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>H</mi>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>. So data is modeled by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\\left( d \\right) = 9.7782{\\left( {1.7125} \\right)^d}\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>d</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>9.7782</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1.7125</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12144","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.9d.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Perform a χ 2 goodness of fit test at the 5% significance level. You should clearly state your hypotheses, the p-value, and your conclusion.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.9—HL modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}